    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-01T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="1056"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1056">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.01/7–144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Naples</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brandt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Naples</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-01T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 1, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>323. From Kirk. At today’s meeting of Advisory Council held under chairmanship
                    Soviet representative, Ambassador Bogomolov, (see my 292, June 27 and my 311,
                    June 29<note n="78" xml:id="d1056fn78">Telegrams not printed.</note>) the
                    Council passed a resolution addressed to Supreme Allied Commander recommending
                    Italian Government be permitted to transfer at an early date from <pb
                        facs="1151" n="1139" xml:id="pg_1139"/> Salerno to Rome. (Text of this
                    resolution is transmitted in my next following telegram.)<note n="79"
                        xml:id="d1056fn79">Telegram 324, July 1, not printed.</note> The condition
                    in resolution stipulating that transfer is recommended in the absence of
                    military objections was inserted upon my recommendation in accordance with
                    instructions of Department transmitted to me in its 271, June 29.<note n="80"
                        xml:id="d1056fn80">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Department; repeated to Algiers, Moscow, London, Cairo for MacVeagh.
                    [Kirk.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Brandt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
